Project Overview

This application is a Clinical Decision Support System (CDSS) prototype designed to predict the risk of coronary artery disease. It utilizes Multiple Imputation by Chained Equations (MICE) to handle missing clinical values and a Random Forest Classifier for risk assessment.
Data Credit & Acknowledgments

The dataset used in this project is the UCI Heart Disease Dataset, accessed via Kaggle.

